I hope you have fun bidding on this beautiful shotgun.Here's what Beretta has to say: The 686 Onyx Pro Field hunting shotgun has all the functional features of our premium over-unders at a particularly attractive price. The premium, oil-finished walnut stock and fore end complement the gloss-finished blued receiver with gold P. Beretta engraving, not found on other 686 Silver Pigeon models. At its heart, it has the best-in-class 686 action, which is compact and low-profile while being extremely strong. Besides 12 and 20 gauge, this shotgun is also available with beautifully scaled-down actions for 28 gauge for a true premium-grade experience. Whether you take it to an upland hunt or to the clay range, the 686 Onyx Pro gives you the flawless performance and the classic looks of a Beretta. The 686 Onyx Pro Field is built on the legendary 686 action, a long-standing favorite among hunters and competitive shooters. It features two conical locking lugs at mid-action, right between the barrels, giving it great locking strength and durability while keeping the action’s profile considerably lower. The advantage is that the eye of the shooter is a lot closer to the plane of his supporting hand: considerably better swing and hand-eye coordination. The 12- or 20-gauge Silver Pigeon has impressed countless hunters for its efficient dimensions and fast handling. But if you see and bring to your shoulder a 686 Onyx Pro in 28 gauge, you will be doubly impressed by the premium feel of the petite action. These are scaled down to fit the smaller gauges without any extra weight or bulkiness--something that you normally find in shotguns prices several times as much as this. title: For Sale:  WWII "RARE" Remington 1903-A4 Sniper
postcontent: "RARE" original WWII Remington M1903-A4 "Sniper". M1903 A4 snipers were  produced in 1943-the only year of production. Nice original C stock with all correct stampings. Includes Redfield scope mount, rare M73B Weaver scope. This rare scope is becoming as valuable as the rifle itself. Stamped US Army designation M73B. Also comes with an original leather sling. Barrel is dated 12-43. Serial number is 4993281. This rifle is in very nice condition for 74 years old. Own a piece of history..........      The sniper rifle was made standard on 14 January 1943. According to Springfield Armory records, on 18 January 1943 Remington Arms was directed to divert from production 20,000 M1903A3 rifles for conversion to the U.S. Rifle M1903A4. Rifles #3REDACTED087 from the first "block" of numbers were diverted, and the first "03-A3" converted was delivered in February 1943.On 20 June 1943 an additional 8,365 M1903A4 rifles were ordered. The number block for these rifles and possible future orders was 4REDACTED000. After this block had been used to 4997045, the receiver marking was changed to "03-A4" and a new series of numbers begun with Z4000000. In March 1944, with receiver Z4002290, production of the M1903A4 was ended with a total of 29,964 M-1903A4 rifles produced.

postcontent: Good Evening,I have a like new & pristine Agawam Arms Cowboy Model M-68, .22short, long and/or long rifle lever-action, single-shot rifle. According to American Rifleman magazine, only 15,000 of these rifles were ever made & it is estimated that only 800 still exist in fully functional condition and this one with a serial number in the 1300's was one of the first ever made. It is in like new condition and appears to have never been exposed to the elements and probably has been fired less than 10 to 20 times. Besides being a wonderful collector's piece, this is probably the "new" shooters most perfect firearm. I purchased the rifle 5 years ago as the first rifle to be given to my 10 year old grandson but unfortunately, he developed & ultimately died from leukemia before we had the chance to enjoy it together. My only hope is that some other Father/Son and/or Grandpa/Grandson get the chance to enjoy it as a team.  The best way to reach me is via text to REDACTED however I will respond to emails but am somewhat slower if you choose that avenue.
